[The occurrence of rabies in Bolivia is more wide spread that
indicated in the previous report of 17 Jul 2011 (see ProMED-mail
archive no 20110717.2164). The 11 Apr 2011 report (ProMED-mail archive
no 20110411.1150) reported just one human case. Now there are 4,
apparently all of canine origin.

A map of the Departments of Bolivia can be accessed at
http://www.boliviabella.com/images/bolivia_facts_maps_provinces.gif.
